30 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
31 Section 1. Pursuant to the Alabama Sunset Law, the
32 Sunset Committee recommends the continuance of the 911 Board
33 until October 1, 2028, with additional recommendation for
34 statutory change as set out in Section 3.
35 Section 2. The existence and functioning of the 911
36 Board, created and functioning pursuant to Sections 11-98-1 to
37 11-98-16, inclusive, Code of Alabama 1975, is continued until
38 October 1 2028, and those code sections are expressly
39 preserved.
40 Section 3. Section 11-98-4.1, Code of Alabama 1975, is
41 amended to read as follows:
42 "§11-98-4.1
43 (a) There is created a statewide 911 Board. The board
44 shall be comprised of 13 members. All appointing authorities
45 shall coordinate their appointments to assure the board
46 membership is inclusive and reflects the racial, gender,
47 geographic, urban, rural, and economic diversity of the state.
48 The 911 Board shall be created effective July 1, 2012, and
49 until the effective date of the statewide 911 charge pursuant
50 to Section 11-98-5, with cooperation of the CMRS Board, shall
51 plan for the implementation of the statewide 911 charge and
52 the distribution of the revenues as provided herein. The
53 reasonable administrative expenses incurred by the 911 Board
54 prior to the implementation of the statewide 911 charge may be
55 deducted from the existing CMRS Fund. Upon the effective date
56 of the new statewide 911 charge, the 911 Board shall replace
