127 (e)(f) The statewide 911 Board shall have the following
128 powers and duties:
129 (1) To develop and publish a 911 Annual Report. In
130 fulfilling this duty, the 911 Board shall monitor trends in
131 voice communications service technology and in enhanced 911
132 service technology, investigate, and incorporate Geographical
133 Information Systems (GIS) mapping and other resources into the
134 report, and include recommended strategies for the efficient
135 and effective delivery of enhanced 911 service. In addition,
136 the board shall study the rates charged for 911 services and
137 make adjustments to the rates as provided in this chapter;
138 recommend any statutory changes necessary to ensure the most
139 efficient and effective delivery of 911 services in Alabama
140 over both the long-term and short-term; and provide a copy of
