144 (2) To administer the 911 Fund and the monthly
145 statewide 911 charge authorized by Section 11-98-5.
146 (3) To distribute revenue in the 911 Fund in accordance
147 with this chapter.
148 (4) To establish policies and procedures, adopted in
149 accordance with the Alabama Administrative Procedure Act, to
150 fund advisory services, grants, and training for districts and
151 to provide funds in accordance with these policies and
152 procedures to the extent funds are available.
153 (5) To make and enter into contracts and agreements
154 necessary or incidental to the performance of its powers and
155 duties under this chapter and to use revenue available to the
156 911 Board under Section 11-98-5 for administrative expenses to
157 pay its obligations under the contracts and agreements.
158 (6) To accept gifts, grants, or other money for the 911
159 Fund.
160 (7) To undertake its duties in a manner that is
161 competitively and technologically neutral as to all voice
162 communications service providers.
163 (8) To administer the deployment and operation of a
164 statewide 911 voice and data system that utilizes emerging
165 communication technologies that are capable of connecting to a
166 911 system and delivering 911 and emergency information to
167 districts. The board shall use its available revenue to pay
168 obligations under the contracts and agreements for a statewide
